##create multiple alerts

To generate multiple alerts you can use the generic @mixin <%= link_to 'mars-build-component', '/documentation/builders/mars-build-component' %> components, visit the page on the builder to better understand how it works and arguments.

The `$mars-alerts` element contains the variations written on a map and its name is generated by adding the prefix that we pass to the mixin.

~~~scss
$mars-alerts: (
  '': (),
  '-warning': (
    background-color: $warning,
    border-color: $warning,
    color: $white
  ),
  '-success': (
    background-color: $success,
    border-color: $success,
    color: $white
  )
);
~~~

In this case we add the first empty element to directly use the prefix as an element, so using this builder it is preferable that we do not add the mars-alert to another element that is not the element to be extended in this case% alert, thus we will obtain less duplicities of css in the result.

<% example_tabs do %>
~~~scss
%alert {
  @include log('üì¶ extend %alert');
  @include mars-alert();
}

@include mars-build-component(
  $prefix: '.alert',
  $extend: '%alert',
  $elements: $mars-alerts
);
~~~

